    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="871"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.203/36</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-09T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.17 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4452. Your 264, July 17, 5 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d871fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_748">p. 748</ref>.</note>
                    Maintenance of discipline among American troops stationed in the United Kingdom.
                    Foreign Office inform me that British military authorities are prepared in <pb
                        facs="0836" n="752" xml:id="pg_752"/> deference to wishes of the United
                    States Government to agree to omission from the proposed agreement of the terms
                    mentioned in the memorandum marked “A” communicated in Embassy’s telegram 9748,
                    April 27, 1 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]<note n="1" xml:id="d871fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante,</hi>
                        <ref target="#pg_744">p. 744</ref>.</note> and inquire whether the United
                    States Government would now be prepared to enter into an agreement on terms
                    similar to those of Franco-American note of January 14 last<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d871fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_736">p. 736</ref>.</note> and
                    if so whether it is desired that British Government submit draft for
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
